<!-- templates/budget-planner/budget-guide.hbs -->
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>

<head>
  <style>
    @page {
      size: A4;
      margin: 12mm;
    }

    body {
      font-family: {{customization.fontFamily}};
      color: #333;
      line-height: 1.4;
    }

    .header {
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 15px;
      border-bottom: 3px solid {{customization.primaryColor}};
      padding-bottom: 10px;
    }

    .title {
      font-size: 26px;
      color: {{customization.primaryColor}};
      margin-bottom: 5px;
    }

    .subtitle {
      font-size: 13px;
      color: #666;
    }

    .formula-box {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, {{customization.primaryColor}}, {{customization.secondaryColor}});
      color: white;
      padding: 18px;
      border-radius: 12px;
      text-align: center;
      margin-bottom: 18px;
    }

    .formula-label {
      font-size: 12px;
      opacity: 0.9;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }

    .formula {
      font-size: 26px;
      font-weight: bold;
      letter-spacing: 2px;
    }

    .formula-note {
      font-size: 12px;
      opacity: 0.85;
      margin-top: 8px;
    }

    .rule-section {
      margin-bottom: 18px;
    }

    .rule-title {
      font-size: 18px;
      color: {{customization.primaryColor}};
      margin-bottom: 12px;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 10px;
    }

    .rule-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
      gap: 12px;
    }

    .rule-card {
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 15px;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .rule-card.needs {
      background: #e3f2fd;
      border: 2px solid #2196f3;
    }

    .rule-card.wants {
      background: #fff3e0;
      border: 2px solid #ff9800;
    }

    .rule-card.savings {
      background: #e8f5e9;
      border: 2px solid #4caf50;
    }

    .rule-percent {
      font-size: 32px;
      font-weight: bold;
      margin-bottom: 5px;
    }

    .rule-card.needs .rule-percent { color: #1976d2; }
    .rule-card.wants .rule-percent { color: #f57c00; }
    .rule-card.savings .rule-percent { color: #388e3c; }

    .rule-name {
      font-size: 14px;
      font-weight: bold;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
    }

    .rule-examples {
      font-size: 11px;
      color: #666;
      line-height: 1.4;
    }

    .middle-section {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 15px;
      margin-bottom: 18px;
    }

    .example-section {
      background: #f8f9fa;
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 15px;
    }

    .example-title {
      font-size: 14px;
      font-weight: bold;
      color: {{customization.primaryColor}};
      margin-bottom: 12px;
    }

    .example-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
      gap: 10px;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .example-item {
      padding: 10px;
      background: white;
      border-radius: 8px;
    }

    .example-amount {
      font-size: 18px;
      font-weight: bold;
      color: {{customization.primaryColor}};
    }

    .example-label {
      font-size: 11px;
      color: #666;
    }

    .your-turn {
      border: 2px dashed {{customization.primaryColor}};
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 15px;
    }

    .your-turn-title {
      font-size: 14px;
      font-weight: bold;
      color: {{customization.primaryColor}};
      margin-bottom: 12px;
      text-align: center;
    }

    .your-turn-row {
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      align-items: center;
      padding: 8px 12px;
      background: #fafafa;
      border-radius: 6px;
      margin-bottom: 6px;
    }

    .your-turn-label {
      font-size: 13px;
    }

    .your-turn-input {
      width: 90px;
      border-bottom: 2px dotted #ccc;
      text-align: right;
      font-weight: bold;
      font-size: 13px;
    }

    .bottom-section {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 15px;
    }

    .tip-box {
      background: #fff8e1;
      border-left: 4px solid #ffc107;
      padding: 12px 15px;
      border-radius: 0 10px 10px 0;
    }

    .tip-title {
      font-weight: bold;
      color: #f57c00;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
      font-size: 13px;
    }

    .tip-text {
      font-size: 12px;
      color: #555;
      line-height: 1.5;
    }

    .mistakes-box {
      background: #ffebee;
      border-left: 4px solid #e91e63;
      padding: 12px 15px;
      border-radius: 0 10px 10px 0;
    }

    .mistakes-title {
      font-weight: bold;
      color: #c2185b;
      margin-bottom: 8px;
      font-size: 13px;
    }

    .mistakes-list {
      font-size: 11px;
      color: #555;
      padding-left: 15px;
      margin: 0;
    }

    .mistakes-list li {
      margin-bottom: 4px;
    }
  </style>
</head>

<body>
  <div class="header">
    <h1 class="title">Mini Guide: How to Budget</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">The basics you need to know (nothing complicated, we promise)</p>
  </div>

  <div class="formula-box">
    <div class="formula-label">The Only Formula You Need</div>
    <div class="formula">INCOME - EXPENSES = BALANCE</div>
    <div class="formula-note">Positive balance = you're saving money! Negative = spending more than you earn.</div>
  </div>

  <div class="rule-section">
    <div class="rule-title">The 50/30/20 Rule (A Starting Point)</div>
    <div class="rule-grid">
      <div class="rule-card needs">
        <div class="rule-percent">50%</div>
        <div class="rule-name">NEEDS</div>
        <div class="rule-examples">
          Rent/mortgage<br>
          Utilities<br>
          Groceries<br>
          Insurance<br>
          Transportation
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="rule-card wants">
        <div class="rule-percent">30%</div>
        <div class="rule-name">WANTS</div>
        <div class="rule-examples">
          Dining out<br>
          Entertainment<br>
          Shopping<br>
          Subscriptions<br>
          Hobbies
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="rule-card savings">
        <div class="rule-percent">20%</div>
        <div class="rule-name">SAVINGS & DEBT</div>
        <div class="rule-examples">
          Emergency fund<br>
          Retirement<br>
          Extra debt payments<br>
          Savings goals
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="middle-section">
    <div class="example-section">
      <div class="example-title">Example: $3,000/month income</div>
      <div class="example-grid">
        <div class="example-item">
          <div class="example-amount">$1,500</div>
          <div class="example-label">Needs (50%)</div>
        </div>
        <div class="example-item">
          <div class="example-amount">$900</div>
          <div class="example-label">Wants (30%)</div>
        </div>
        <div class="example-item">
          <div class="example-amount">$600</div>
          <div class="example-label">Savings (20%)</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="your-turn">
      <div class="your-turn-title">Your Turn: Calculate Your 50/30/20</div>
      <div class="your-turn-row">
        <span class="your-turn-label">My monthly income:</span>
        <span class="your-turn-input">$ _______</span>
      </div>
      <div class="your-turn-row">
        <span class="your-turn-label">50% for Needs:</span>
        <span class="your-turn-input">$ _______</span>
      </div>
      <div class="your-turn-row">
        <span class="your-turn-label">30% for Wants:</span>
        <span class="your-turn-input">$ _______</span>
      </div>
      <div class="your-turn-row">
        <span class="your-turn-label">20% for Savings/Debt:</span>
        <span class="your-turn-input">$ _______</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bottom-section">
    <div class="tip-box">
      <div class="tip-title">Pro Tip</div>
      <div class="tip-text">
        This rule is a <strong>guideline</strong>, not a strict law. If your rent is 40% of income, that's okay â€” adjust the other categories.
        The goal is awareness and balance, not perfection. Start where you are and improve over time.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mistakes-box">
      <div class="mistakes-title">Common Mistakes to Avoid</div>
      <ul class="mistakes-list">
        <li>Not tracking small purchases (they add up!)</li>
        <li>Forgetting irregular expenses (car repairs, gifts)</li>
        <li>Being too strict (you'll burn out)</li>
        <li>Not adjusting when income changes</li>
        <li>Skipping the "pay yourself first" rule</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>

</html>
